<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="873" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d873">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">661.4116/33: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-28T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 28—3:56
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>864. I learn that Krassin who arrived in London last night will
                                connect this afternoon with the Permanent Committee of the Supreme
                                Economic Council accompanied by the other members of the Russian
                                trade delegation. Arrangements are being made for Prime Minister to
                                interview him in spite of the considerable opposition still existing
                                against any proposal to resume political relations with the Soviet
                                Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>